==English==
===Noun===
'''pout'''

#The young of some birds, as grouse; a young fowl.
#(The shape of) one's mouth when pouting

====Translations====
*French: [[boude]] (2)

===Verb===
'''to pout'''

#To shoot pouts
#To push out one's lips
#To sulk, (to pretend) being ill-tempered

====Translations====
*French: [[bouder]] (2, 3)
*German: [[schürzen]] (2), [[schmollen]] (3)

===Derived terms===
*[[eelpout]], [[eel-pout]]

